                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/3721.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-25T21:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 25, 1912—9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A British war vessel will go to Mexican Pacific coast to aid British colonists.
                    This will probably be the signal for visits on both sides by other nations.</p>
                <p>Isthmus situation bad; also Oaxaca. Consul at Saltillo reports capture of Cuatro
                    Cienegas by rebels. General situation the same, with signs of unrest in this
                    city.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
